  "prompt": "What is meant by the hindi term 'bakchodi'?",
  "response": "The Hindi term 'bakchodi' (\u092c\u0915\u0935\u093e\u0938) is colloquial and informal, often used in casual conversations. It generally refers to nonsensical talk, idle chatter, or time-wasting activities. It can also imply joking around or engaging in frivolous banter. The term is derived from 'bakwas,' which means rubbish or nonsense, but 'bakchodi' carries a lighter, more playful connotation. \n\nPlease note that the usage and perceived offensiveness of the term can vary based on context and the relationship between the people involved in the conversation.",
